input() always be in string type. Check the same using type().

Convert one datatype to another using following,
float() - To convert any datatype into float (decimals). EG: 1.23
int() - To convert any datatype into integer. EG: 1
str() - To convert any datatype into string (that comes inside quotes). EG: "1.23"

Python uses PEMDAS for mathematical operations.
P - Parantheses
E - Exponent
M - Multiplication
D - Division
A - Addition
S - Subtraction

To round off any decimals, use round(digit, decimal_places) (EG: round(1.2308, 2))
or use floor division, EG: 8 // 3 - 2.67 (natural round off the decimal places to 2)

Integer and string can't be printed in same statement. To do so use f-String

Mark = 55
print(f"You mark is {Mark}")

Using the above learning, done a simple tip calculator project.
